  <p>David Tvildiani Medical University is a well-known medical university in Tbilisi, Georgia. The university was founded in 1989 and has since become a leading institution for medical education in the region. In this comprehensive guide, we will explore the history, mission, vision, programs, faculty, and other aspects of David Tvildiani Medical University.</p>
<h3>HISTORY</h3>
<p>David Tvildiani Medical University was founded in 1989 by Dr. Dimitri Tvildiani, a prominent surgeon and professor of medicine. The university was established with a vision to provide quality medical education to students from around the world, and over the years, it has remained committed to this goal.</p>
<p>The university started with a small group of students, but it has now grown to become a well-respected institution that attracts students from all over the world. In 2011, the university was granted full accreditation by the Ministry of Education and Science of Georgia.</p>


