<h3>Mission and Vision:</h3>
<p>The mission of David Tvildiani Medical University is to provide high-quality medical education that meets the needs of students from all backgrounds. The university aims to produce well-trained and skilled medical professionals who can contribute to the improvement of global healthcare.</p>

<p>The vision of the university is to become a leading institution for medical education and research in the region. The university aims to achieve this by providing innovative and effective teaching methods, modern facilities, and a supportive learning environment.</p>
<h3>Programs:</h3>
<p>David Tvildiani Medical University offers undergraduate, graduate, and postgraduate programs in various medical fields. The university's programs are designed to meet the needs of students from diverse backgrounds and prepare them for successful careers in medicine.</p>
<p>The undergraduate program in medicine is a six-year program that covers a wide range of subjects, including anatomy, physiology, pharmacology, and clinical medicine. The program is taught in English, and the curriculum is designed to meet international standards.</p>
<p>The university also offers a graduate program in medicine, which is a three-year program that focuses on advanced medical knowledge and clinical skills. The program is designed for students who have completed their undergraduate studies in medicine.</p>
<p>The university also offers postgraduate programs in various medical fields, including surgery, pediatrics, obstetrics and gynecology, and internal medicine.</p>

<h3>Faculty:</h3>
<p>The faculty of David Tvildiani Medical University comprises highly qualified and experienced medical professionals who are dedicated to providing quality education to students. The faculty members are from diverse backgrounds and have expertise in various medical fields.</p>
<p>The faculty members use modern teaching methods, including lectures, seminars, and practical sessions, to help students learn effectively. They also provide guidance and support to students throughout their academic journey.</p>
<h3>Facilities:</h3>
<p>David Tvildiani Medical University has modern facilities that provide students with a comfortable and supportive learning environment. The university has well-equipped lecture halls, laboratories, libraries, and computer centers that cater to the needs of students.</p>
<p>The university also has clinical training facilities that provide students with hands-on training in various medical fields. The clinical training facilities are located in leading hospitals in Tbilisi and other cities in Georgia.</p>



<h3>Fee Structure:</h3>
<p>The fee structure of David Tvildiani Medical University is competitive and affordable compared to other medical universities in Europe and America. The tuition fee for the undergraduate program in medicine is around $7000 per year. The fee for the graduate and postgraduate programs varies depending on the field of study.</p>

